.TH "xprt_sock_sendmsg" 9 "xprt_sock_sendmsg" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
xprt_sock_sendmsg \- write an xdr_buf directly to a socket
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" xprt_sock_sendmsg
.BI "(struct socket *sock "  ","
.BI "struct msghdr *msg "  ","
.BI "struct xdr_buf *xdr "  ","
.BI "unsigned int base "  ","
.BI "rpc_fraghdr marker "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *sent_p "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sock" 12
open socket to send on
.IP "msg" 12
socket message metadata
.IP "xdr" 12
xdr_buf containing this request
.IP "base" 12
starting position in the buffer
.IP "marker" 12
stream record marker field
.IP "sent_p" 12
return the total number of bytes successfully queued for sending
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return values:
On success, returns zero and fills in \fIsent_p\fP.
-ENOTSOCK if  \fIsock\fP is not a struct socket.
